HEADWORD: Eserine
<hw>Es"er*ine</hw> <pr>(?; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From native
name of the Calabar bean: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧s⟦eacute⟧rine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
alkaloid found in the Calabar bean, and the seed of <spn>Physostigma
venenosum</spn>; physostigmine. It is used in ophthalmic surgery for its
effect in contracting the pupil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Esexual</ent>⟦br⟧
